  "suggestion": "Efficiency scales with metabolic specialization—not all organisms should be generalists. Diversity and efficiency improve together when genomes adopt different energy strategies.; Efficiency at 0.523 is the critical bottleneck—the weakest metric by far, and it directly limits the composite goal. Within beauty, diversityOfForms (0.456) is failing; organisms are too morphologically similar. The alive organisms plateau at age 500 with moderate energy (15-32), suggesting they're surviving but not thriving. Root cause: organisms are either burning energy inefficiently or not optimizing resource gathering. Solution: (1) Lower movement costs via reduced moveSpeed and explorationDrive, (2) increase energyConserve to stretch resources, (3) vary resourceAttraction and harvestThreshold across genomes to create metabolic diversity and force specialization.",
